ough investing in employees, infrastructure, technology, and community outr=
each. The department continually serves the community by limiting and preve=
nting energy outages, protecting residents and visitors from electrical haz=
ards, and providing a competitive price to residents and businesses.   The =
Energy Department does not collect utility payments, but they do house the =
city's electrical maintenance, projects, forestry, and power systems divisi=
ons.</p>
